Definition: a movement in literature and art during the 17th and 18th centuries in Europe that favored rationality and restraint and strict forms
Example: classicism often derived its models from the ancient Greeks and Romans
Synonyms: adj, pert, classicistic, noun, person, classicist, romanticism, classicalism, humanistic_discipline, attribute, artistic_style, a, movement, in, literature, and, art, during, the, th, centuries, Europe, that, favored, rationality, restraint, strict, forms, often, derived, its, models, from, ancient, Greeks, Romans
Category: noun.cognition
